            <fr:title text="embeddings are propositional"><fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-003K.xml" title="embedding" addr="forest://erct/erct-003K" type="local">embeddings</fr:link> are <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-001T.xml" title="n-truncated map" addr="forest://erct/erct-001T" type="local">propositional</fr:link></fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Lemma</fr:taxon>
            <fr:meta name="source">
  
  
  <fr:link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-0048.agda" type="external">erct-0048.agda</fr:link>
</fr:meta>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter><html:p>Any <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-003K.xml" title="embedding" addr="forest://erct/erct-003K" type="local">embedding</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  A\to  B]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-001T.xml" title="n-truncated map" addr="forest://erct/erct-001T" type="local">propositional</fr:link>.</html:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="forest://erct/jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>2</fr:month><fr:day>18</fr:day></fr:date><fr:addr>forest://erct/erct-0048/0</fr:addr><fr:route>https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-0048/0.xml</fr:route><fr:title text="embeddings are propositional › forest://erct/erct-0048/0"><fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-0048.xml" title="embeddings are propositional" addr="forest://erct/erct-0048" type="local"><fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-003K.xml" title="embedding" addr="forest://erct/erct-003K" type="local">embeddings</fr:link> are <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-001T.xml" title="n-truncated map" addr="forest://erct/erct-001T" type="local">propositional</fr:link></fr:link> › forest://erct/erct-0048/0</fr:title><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
 <html:p>We must check that for every <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[b:B]]></fr:tex>, the <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-001Q.xml" title="fiber" addr="forest://erct/erct-001Q" type="local">fiber</fr:link> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> at <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[b]]></fr:tex> is a <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-001I.xml" title="proposition" addr="forest://erct/erct-001I" type="local">proposition</fr:link>. Fixing <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[u_0,u_1:\mathsf {fiber}\,f\,b]]></fr:tex> we must check that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[u_0=u_1]]></fr:tex>. We let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen a_0,p_0\right \rparen \mathclose {}
\equiv  u_0]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen a_1,p_1\right \rparen \mathclose {}
\equiv  u_1]]></fr:tex> so that we have <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[p_0\colon  fa_0=b]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[p_1\colon  fa_1=b]]></fr:tex>. Invoking the <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-0010.xml" title="path object" addr="forest://erct/erct-0010" type="local">path object</fr:link> structure on <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-001Q.xml" title="fiber" addr="forest://erct/erct-001Q" type="local">fibers</fr:link> (<fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-001R.xml" title="path object structure on fibers" addr="forest://erct/erct-001R" type="local">Example <fr:contextual-number addr="forest://erct/erct-001R" /></fr:link>), it suffices to exhibit the following data:</html:p>
 <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
  \begin {aligned}
   \phi &\colon  a_0 = a_1\\
   \psi &\colon  p_0 = \mathsf {act}_{f}\phi \cdot  p_1
  \end {aligned}
 ]]></fr:tex>

  <html:p>As <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> is an <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-001K.xml" title="contractible types are propositions" addr="forest://erct/erct-001K" type="local">embedding</fr:link>, the map <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathsf {act}_{f}\colon  a_0 = a_1 \to  fa_0 = fa_1]]></fr:tex> has an <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-000W.xml" title="inverse" addr="forest://erct/erct-000W" type="local">inverse</fr:link> 
 <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathopen {}\left \lparen \mathsf {act}_{f}^{-1},\epsilon ,\eta ,\chi \right \rparen \mathclose {}]]></fr:tex>
.</html:p>

 <html:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\alpha  \colon  fa_0 = fa_1]]></fr:tex> be the concatenation <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[p_0\cdot  p_1^{-1}]]></fr:tex>. Therefore we may define:</html:p>

 <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
  \begin {aligned}
   \phi &\colon  a_0 = a_1\\
   \phi &:\equiv  \mathsf {act}_{f}^{-1} \alpha 
  \end {aligned}
 ]]></fr:tex>

 <html:p>To define <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\psi  \colon  p_0=\mathsf {act}_{f}\phi \cdot  p_1]]></fr:tex> we use the counit of our <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-000W.xml" title="inverse" addr="forest://erct/erct-000W" type="local">inverse</fr:link> as we have <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\epsilon  \alpha  \colon  \mathsf {act}_{f}\phi  = p_0\cdot  p_1^{-1}]]></fr:tex>. Thus concatenating on either side with <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[p_1]]></fr:tex> we have our goal, modulo the laws of identification concatenation and symmetry respectively.</html:p>
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
</fr:mainmatter>
