            <fr:title text="inverse">inverse</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
            <fr:meta name="source">
  
  
  <fr:link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-000W.agda" type="external">erct-000W.agda</fr:link>
</fr:meta>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>An <html:em><html:strong>inverse</html:strong></html:em> to a function <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  A \to  B]]></fr:tex> is defined to be a <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-000X.xml" title="quasi-inverse" addr="forest://erct/erct-000X" type="local">quasi-inverse</fr:link> equipped with an additional higher coherence <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\chi  \colon  \mathsf {act}_{f}\circ  \eta  \sim  \epsilon \circ  f]]></fr:tex> in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f\circ  g \circ  f \sim  f]]></fr:tex> relating the (<html:em>a priori</html:em> incoherent) unit and the counit of the quasi-inverse. We will refer to a function <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  A\to  B]]></fr:tex> equipped with an inverse as an <html:em><html:strong>invertible function</html:strong></html:em>.</html:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
